OL,3,CCutting taxes will lead to worse
OL,4,Cpublic services, IFS warns ahead of
OL,5,Cbudget
OL,7,FAs things stand, the IFS estimates the
OL,8,Fbudgets of unprotected departments -
OL,9,Flocal government, the courts, HMRC and
OL,10,Fprisons - require cash top-ups of #20
OL,11,Fbillion a year by 2028/29 to avoid a
OL,12,Freturn to "austerity".
OL,14,FIf the chancellor does reduce the
OL,15,Fplanned rate of growth in spending on
OL,16,Fpublic services from 0.9% to 0.75% in
OL,17,Fthe Budget, the IFS calculates it
OL,18,Fwould free up #3 billion a year for
OL,19,Ftax cuts but at the expense of the
OL,20,Fbudgets of these unprotected areas.
