OL,7,FInflation is fading faster than the
OL,8,FOBR forecast last November but the
OL,9,Foutlook for growth remains weak in the
OL,10,Fshort-term.
OL,12,FThe chancellor doesn't have much room
OL,13,Ffor manoeuvre in his Budget but he
OL,14,Fdoes have choices he can make.
OL,16,FThe IFS argues that, if Jeremy Hunt
OL,17,Fdecides to prioritise tax cuts before
OL,18,Fthe election, he will be doing so at
OL,19,Fthe expense of the quality of public
OL,20,Fservices after the election.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G13/17
